  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Portraits and Poses,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, is a notable academic contribution, enriched by a commercial linkage evidenced by its availability on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Portraits and Poses,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, represents a significant scholarly output, although it has yet to accrue citations or engage in broader community discourse. The absence of mentions across recognized platforms such as Wikipedia, Reddit, or Bluesky indicates limited public engagement or discourse surrounding the publication at this time.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite this, the work reflects a strong commercial linkage, scoring high in its presence on commerce-oriented platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, which suggests potential reader interest and market viability. This aspect highlights a degree of reach in the commercial sector, potentially indicating its relevance or appeal to a broader audience.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the book does have a noted strength in sustainability and policy relevance, with alignment to one Sustainable Development Goal. This aspect suggests that \"Portraits and Poses\" might engage with contemporary issues and contribute to relevant discussions within policy or environmental contexts, albeit without exhaustive evidence of its influence indicated in the available metrics.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while the lack of citations and community engagement may seem limiting, the existing commercial aspects reflect an underlying potential for wider acceptance and application of the work, suggesting a pathway to increased visibility and impact in academic and broader societal discussions in the future.</p>",
